# Testing Rules

## Framework
- Use **Vitest** for all tests (unit, integration, component)
- Colocate test files: `users.service.ts` → `users.service.test.ts`
- Config per package: each package has its own `vitest.config.ts`

## Coverage Target
- Minimum 80% line coverage for `packages/`
- Focus on testing business logic and API endpoints
- Don't test framework internals or simple type definitions

## Test Structure
- Use `describe` for grouping, `it` for individual tests
- Descriptive test names: `it('returns 404 when user does not exist')`
- Follow Arrange-Act-Assert (AAA) pattern
- One assertion per test (logical assertion — multiple `expect` calls are fine if testing one behavior)

```typescript
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';

describe('UserService', () => {
  describe('findById', () => {
    it('returns the user when found', async () => {
      // Arrange
      const userId = 'clx123';

      // Act
      const user = await userService.findById(userId);

      // Assert
      expect(user).toMatchObject({ id: userId });
    });

    it('returns null when user does not exist', async () => {
      const user = await userService.findById('nonexistent');
      expect(user).toBeNull();
    });
  });
});
```

## API Testing (Hono)
- Use `app.request()` — no HTTP server needed
- Test status codes, response body, and headers
- Test validation errors (invalid input → 400)
- Test authentication/authorization if applicable

```typescript
describe('POST /api/users', () => {
  it('creates a user with valid input', async () => {
    const res = await app.request('/api/users', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ email: 'test@example.com', name: 'Test' }),
    });
    expect(res.status).toBe(201);
  });

  it('returns 400 with invalid email', async () => {
    const res = await app.request('/api/users', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ email: 'invalid', name: 'Test' }),
    });
    expect(res.status).toBe(400);
  });
});
```

## Mocking
- Mock external services (HTTP APIs, email, etc.) — never mock internal modules
- Use `vi.mock()` for module mocking, `vi.fn()` for function mocking
- Prefer dependency injection over module mocking when possible
- Reset mocks between tests: `afterEach(() => { vi.restoreAllMocks(); })`

## Component Testing
- Use `@testing-library/react` for component tests
- Test behavior, not implementation details
- Query by role, label, or text — never by test ID unless necessary
- Avoid snapshot tests (brittle, low signal)
